Name: AMARANT
Description:
KS
ko76
Early red cabbage, ready to harvest from mid June. Short stem with flat layered leaves. Round, smallish heads. Thanks to its fast growth can be cultivated rather late in the year, even at higher elevations.
Use: fresh (storage)
Type: red cabbage

Explanations: ProSpecieRara: This variety has been awarded by ProSpecieRara as a rare or old variety. ProSpecieRara is a foundation dedicated to preserving the diversity of rare plant varieties. In long-term cooperation with ProSpecieRara, Sativa is active in the important preservation and cultivation of these traditional varieties.
Name: KALIBOS
Description:
ko06
Pointed cabbage with loose filling and little stalk. Tender leaves with a mild-sweet aroma and therefore good to use raw. After a cultivation period of 3 - 4 months the heads weighing approx. 1.5 kg can be harvested.
Use: fresh
Type: red cabbage

Explanations:
Bioverita: This variety is an organic, newly bred, variety. It has been cultivated from the very outset in organic conditions, to best adapt to organic cultivation. Varieties that carry the Bioverita label are reproducible and fertile, and aim to offer an alternative to hybrid-seeds to professional gardeners.
Precision seeds: The seeds are calibrated and have an increased germination capacity. The seeds are sold per piece.
Name: RODYNDA
Description:
KS
  ko72
Vigorously growing variety, short stem, strong rooting system, tough outer leaf. Tall oval head with short inside stem, stores well.
Use: storage
Type: red cabbage
